spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: PCI is a complex interface with a wide variety of uses in computer and embedded systems applications. CorePCIF expands on the popular CorePCI by adding a FIFO interface. CorePCIF is the most versatile FPGA PCI core available because it is capable of 33/66 MHz operation with either 32 or 64-bit bus widths in master, target, and master/target configurations. The master configuraation includes a built-in DMA controller. CorePCIF includes a user testbench for system verification and a comprehensive testbench too verify core performance against the datasheet
